---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Justin Doone"
  description="Digital marketing strategist working at the intersection of asset management, real estate, and brand. Approach, ethos, and background."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 pt-20 md:pt-32 pb-16">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-8">About</p>
    <h1 class="heading-display text-5xl md:text-7xl text-ink mb-10 leading-[0.95]">
      I build the marketing engines behind serious investment products.
    </h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-6">
      I'm a Toronto-based marketing strategist working at the intersection of asset management, private equity, and real estate development. My work covers the full stack — from positioning and brand systems through campaign execution and the analytics that prove what worked.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
      Clients have included <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Greybrook Capital</strong>, <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Clifton Blake</strong>, <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Roxborough Communities</strong>, and a handful of consumer brands looking to expand internationally.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW I WORK -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 py-16 rule-top">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-8">How I work</p>
    <div class="space-y-10">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-4 md:gap-10">
        <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-ink">Strategy first</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          Every project starts with the same question — who is this for, and what do we need them to believe? Tactics without a clear answer to that question are how marketing budgets disappear.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-4 md:gap-10">
        <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-ink">Integrated by default</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          Channels are not strategies. I plan from a single narrative and adapt it across paid media, content, owned platforms, and sales enablement — so the prospect sees one consistent story, not nine disconnected campaigns.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-4 md:gap-10">
        <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-ink">Measure what matters</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          Vanity metrics are easy. I instrument campaigns so we can tell the difference between reach and revenue — and adjust based on the gap between them.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[140px_1fr] gap-4 md:gap-10">
        <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-ink">Compliance-aware</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          In regulated industries, the best marketing isn't the loudest — it's the marketing that gets through review on the first pass. I write to the compliance line, not over it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ETHOS -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 py-16 rule-top">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-8">Ethos</p>
    <blockquote class="heading-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-ink leading-tight max-w-3xl mb-8">
      "Marketing is just compounding interest on clarity. The earlier you get the story right, the more every dollar afterward is worth."
    </blockquote>
    <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
      I'm allergic to jargon, suspicious of "thought leadership," and tired of decks that are 80 pages of context for one good idea. The best work I've done is usually the work I had to fight hardest to keep simple.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 py-16 rule-top">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-6">Get in touch</p>
    <h2 class="heading-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-ink mb-8">
      Have a project that needs a clearer story?
    </h2>
    <a
      href="mailto:hello@justindoone.com"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-ink text-paper px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-accent transition-colors"
    >
      hello@justindoone.com
      <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
    </a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
